cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about text generation using neural language models and Generative Adversarial Nets (GANs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of GAN variants, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the area of generative models. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second likely category. The paper proposes two metric functions to measure the distributional difference between real text and generated text, which involves artificial intelligence and natural language processing, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the third likely category. The paper also mentions the use of adversarial learning, which is a common technique in neural networks, and thus, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the failure of language GANs, which involves evaluating the performance of models, and thus, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the fifth likely category.
